timeline.message:
State the option to reference templates in cluster

The option to use templates already defined in the cluster is not explicitly stated in the docs, but can be found out from an error message.

'''{
  "error" : {
    "root_cause" : [
      {
        "type" : "x_content_parse_exception",
        "reason" : "[7:7] [script_with_id] failed to parse field [template]"
      }
    ],
    "type" : "x_content_parse_exception",
    "reason" : "[7:7] [rank_eval] failed to parse field [templates]",
    "caused_by" : {
      "type" : "x_content_parse_exception",
      "reason" : "[7:7] [script_with_id] failed to parse field [template]",
      "caused_by" : {
        "type" : "illegal_argument_exception",
        "reason" : "must specify either [source] for an inline script or [id] for a stored script"
      }
    }
  },
  "status" : 400
}'''
